<span id="v.iv.viii.xx"></span>

<span id="v.iv.viii.xx-p1"></span> <span class="c11"><span
id="v.iv.viii.xx-p1.1"></span>Chapter 20.—</span>34.  Polianus of
Mileum <span id="fr_1657"></span>[1658](#fn_1657.md) said:  "It is right
that a heretic should be baptized in the holy Church." <span
id="fr_1658"></span>[1659](#fn_1658.md)

<span id="v.iv.viii.xx-p4"></span>35.  Nothing, indeed, could be
expressed more shortly.  But I think this too is short:  It is right
that the baptism of Christ should not be depreciated in the Church of
Christ.

